defs.docs: Semantic version parsing and comparison.

defs.name: Numeric
defs.docs: An identifier that's solely numbers.

defs.name: AlphaNumeric
defs.docs: An identifier with letters and numbers.

defs.name: Identifier
defs.docs: An identifier in the pre-release or build metadata.

defs.name: Version
defs.value: Version { major, minor, patch, pre, build }
defs.docs: Represents a version number conforming to the semantic versioning scheme.

defs.name: major
defs.docs: The major version, to be incremented on incompatible changes.

defs.name: minor
defs.docs:
The minor version, to be incremented when functionality is added in a
 backwards-compatible manner.

defs.name: patch
defs.docs:
The patch version, to be incremented when backwards-compatible bug
 fixes are made.

defs.name: pre
defs.docs: The pre-release version identifier, if one exists.

defs.name: build
defs.docs: The build metadata, ignored when determining version precedence.

defs.name: NonAsciiIdentifier
defs.docs: All identifiers must be ASCII.

defs.name: IncorrectParse
defs.docs: The version was mis-parsed.

defs.name: GenericFailure
defs.docs: Any other failure.

defs.name: ParseError
defs.docs:
A `ParseError` is returned as the `Err` side of a `Result` when a version is
 attempted to be parsed.

defs.name: parse
defs.docs: Parse a string into a semver object.

defs.name: increment_patch
defs.docs: Increments the patch number for this Version (Must be mutable)

defs.name: increment_minor
defs.docs: Increments the minor version number for this Version (Must be mutable)

defs.name: increment_major
defs.docs: Increments the major version number for this Version (Must be mutable)

defs.name: VersionReq
defs.docs:
A `VersionReq` is a struct containing a list of predicates that can apply to ranges of version
 numbers. Matching operations can then be done with the `VersionReq` against a particular
 version to see if it satisfies some or all of the constraints.

defs.name: InvalidVersionRequirement
defs.docs: The given version requirement is invalid.

defs.name: OpAlreadySet
defs.docs: You have already provided an operation, such as `=`, `~`, or `^`. Only use one.

defs.name: InvalidSigil
defs.docs: The sigil you have written is not correct.

defs.name: VersionComponentsMustBeNumeric
defs.docs: All components of a version must be numeric.

defs.name: MajorVersionRequired
defs.docs: At least a major version is required.

defs.name: UnimplementedVersionRequirement
defs.docs: An unimplemented version requirement.

defs.name: ReqParseError
defs.docs:
A `ReqParseError` is returned from methods which parse a string into a `VersionReq`. Each
 enumeration is one of the possible errors that can occur.

defs.name: any
defs.docs:
`any()` is a factory method which creates a `VersionReq` with no constraints. In other
 words, any version will match against it.

defs.name: parse
defs.docs:
`parse()` is the main constructor of a `VersionReq`. It turns a string like `"^1.2.3"`
 and turns it into a `VersionReq` that matches that particular constraint.

defs.name: exact
defs.docs: `exact()` is a factory method which creates a `VersionReq` with one exact constraint.

defs.name: matches
defs.docs: `matches()` matches a given `Version` against this `VersionReq`.
